This paper deals with a computer vision problem of counting people in an image, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a deep learning framework that uses attention mechanism, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of occlusion and perspective distortion, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and computer graphics (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.MM and cs.CR.
